<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="plone">

<body>
<metal:main fill-slot="main">

    <h1 class="documentFirstHeading"
        i18n:translate="heading_accessibility_info">Accessibility</h1>

    <div id="content-core">


      <p><tal:i18n i18n:translate="description_accessibility_info">
            This site uses the open source Content Management System <a href="https://plone.org" i18n:name="plone">Plone</a>.
            It meets the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines
	    (<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/"><acronym i18n:name="wcag"
                  title="Web Content Accessibility Guidelines"
                  i18n:attributes="title title_wcag;">WCAG</acronym> v2.1</a>) level 'AA' for people with disabilities,
            including blindness and low vision, deafness and hearing loss, learning disabilities,
            cognitive limitations, limited movement, speech disabilities, photosensitivity,
            and combinations of these.</tal:i18n></p>
         <p><tal:i18n i18n:translate="description_accessibility_info2">
            It is also accessible to content authors with disabilities per the level 'AA' Authoring Tool Accessibility Guidelines
            (<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/ATAG20/"><acronym i18n:name="atag"
                 title="Authoring Tool Accessibility Guidelines"
                 i18n:attributes="title title_atag;">ATAG</acronym> 2.0</a>).
         </tal:i18n>
        </p>

        <h2 i18n:translate="heading_accessibility_statement">Accessibility Statement</h2>

        <p i18n:translate="description_accessibility_statement">
        This site was designed to accommodate the different ways people access and use the Internet.
        </p>

        <h3 i18n:translate="heading_validation">Validation</h3>

        <p i18n:translate="description_validation">
       The site uses assistive technology like WAI-ARIA roles to the current best practices;
       however, site standards and content vary over time.

        If this web site does not validate correctly, please contact the
        <span i18n:name="site_admin"><a href="/contact-info"
              tal:attributes="href string:${context/portal_url}/contact-info"
              i18n:translate="label_site_admin">site administration</a></span>.
        </p>

        <p i18n:translate="description_wcag_aa_rating">
        A number of checkpoints in
        <acronym i18n:name="wcag"
                 title="Web Content Accessibility Guidelines"
                 i18n:attributes="title title_wcag;">WCAG</acronym> 2.1 and <acronym i18n:name="atag"
                 title="Authoring Tool Accessibility Guidelines"
                 i18n:attributes="title title_atag;">ATAG</acronym> 2.0 guidelines are
        subjective; there may be instances where interpretations vary.
        </p>

    	<h3 i18n:translate="heading_vpat">Voluntary Product Accessibility Template (VPAT)</h3>
        <p i18n:translate="description_vpat">
          View
            <a title="Plone's Voluntary Product Accessibility Template (VPAT)"
               href="https://plone.org/plone-vpat.pdf/view"
               i18n:attributes="title title_plone_vpat;">
               Plone's VPAT
            </a>
            <a href="https://www.state.gov/m/irm/impact/126340.htm">
                <acronym i18n:name="vpat" title="About VPAT" i18n:attributes="title title_vpat;">(about VPAT)</acronym>
            </a>
        </p>

    </div>

</metal:main>
</body>
</html>
